Each instance of `Console.ReadLine()` will read _a different line_. You should read the value once at the top of the loop.

At the moment your code does this:

1. Read line (request user input).
2. Can it be parsed to int? No.
3. Read line (request user input _again_)
4. Is it equal to &quot;quit&quot;? Yes.
5. Break

You should read the line once per iteration of the loop:

	while (counter &lt; 10)
	{
		string line = Console.ReadLine();
		bool success = int.TryParse(line, out number);
		if (success == true)
		{
			total[counter] = number;
			counter++;
		}
		else if (line == &quot;quit&quot;)
		{
			break;
		}
		else
		{
			Console.WriteLine(&quot;Wrong input.&quot;);
		}
	}

This will now request user input _once_ and store the result in `line`. You can then perform whatever checks you need on this value before iterating.

